---
title: <%= site.title %>
description: <%= site.description %>
---
<article id="include-yfm-lodash">
  <div class="title">
    {{title}} => {{site.title}}
  </div>
  <p class="description"> {{description}} </p>
  <p class="description"> {{site.description}} </p>
</article>

Note that the YAML front matter is "borrowing" data from the <code>site</code> object, which is defined in the Grunt config.

So in this example, <code>\{{title}}</code> will yield the same result as <code>\{{site.title}}</code>, and <code>\{{description}}</code> will
yield the same result as <code>\{{site.description}}</code>